                                "mergeField": "%3Cdiv%3E%3Cspan%20style=%22font-size:%2012pt;%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EGuidance%20for%20Disclosure%20408-1%3C/strong%3E%3C/span%3E%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3EThe%20process%20for%20identifying%20operations%20and%20suppliers,%20as%20specified%20in%20Disclosure%20408-1,%20can%20reflect%20the%20reporting%20organization&rsquo;s%20approach%20to%20risk%20assessment%20on%20this%20issue.%20It%20can%20also%20draw%20from%20recognized%20international%20data%20sources,%20such%20as%20the%20ILO%20Information%20and%20reports%20on%20the%20application%20of%20Conventions&nbsp;and%20Recommendations.%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3EWhen%20reporting%20the%20measures%20taken,%20the%20organization%20can%20refer%20to%20the%20ILO%20&lsquo;Tripartite%20Declaration%20of%20Principles%20Concerning%20Multinational%20Enterprises%20and%20Social%20Policy&rsquo;%20and%20Organisation%20for%20Economic%20Co-operation%20and%20Development%20(OECD)%20OECD%20Guidelines%20for%20Multinational%20Enterprises%20for%20further%20guidance.%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3EIn%20the%20context%20of%20the%20GRI%20Standards,%20a%20&lsquo;young%20worker&rsquo;%20is%20defined%20as%20a%20person%20above%20the%20applicable%20minimum%20working%20age%20and%20younger%20than%2018%20years%20of%20age.%20Note%20that%20Disclosure%20408-1%20does%20not%20require%20quantitative%20reporting%20on%20child%20labor%20or%20the%20number%20of%20young%20workers.%20Rather,%20it%20asks%20for%20reporting%20on%20the%20operations%20and%20suppliers%20considered%20to%20have%20significant%20risk%20for%20incidents%20of%20child%20labor%20or%20young%20workers%20exposed%20to%20hazardous%20work.%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E&nbsp;%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E%3Cstrong%3E%20Background%20%3C/strong%3E%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3EChild%20labor%20is%20subject%20to%20ILO%20Conventions%20138%20&lsquo;Minimum%20Age%20Convention&rsquo;%20(ILO%20Convention%20138)%20and%20182%20&lsquo;Worst%20Forms%20of%20Child%20Labour%20Convention&rsquo;%20(ILO%20Convention%20182).%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E&lsquo;Child%20labor&rsquo;%20refers%20to%20an%20abuse,%20which%20is%20not%20to%20be%20confused%20with%20&lsquo;children%20working&rsquo;%20or%20with%20&lsquo;young%20persons%20working&rsquo;,%20which%20may%20not%20be%20abuses%20as%20stipulated%20in%20ILO%20Convention%20138.%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3EThe%20minimum%20age%20for%20working%20differs%20by%20country.%20ILO%20Convention%20138%20specifies%20a%20minimum%20age%20of%2015%20years%20or%20the%20age%20of%20completion%20of%20compulsory%20schooling%20(whichever%20is%20higher).%20However,%20there%20is%20an%20exception%20for%20certain%20countries%20where%20economies%20and%20educational%20facilities%20are%20insufficiently%20developed%20and%20a%20minimum%20age%20of%2014%20years%20might%20apply.%20These%20countries%20of%20exception%20are%20specified%20by%20the%20ILO%20in%20response%20to%20special%20application%20by%20the%20country%20concerned,%20and%20in%20consultation%20with%20representative%20organizations%20of%20employers%20and%20workers.%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3EILO%20Convention%20138%20stipulates%20that%20&lsquo;national%20laws%20or%20regulations%20may%20permit%20the%20employment%20or%20work&nbsp;of%20persons%2013%20to%2015%20years%20of%20age%20on%20light%20work%20which%20is%20(a)%20not%20likely%20to%20be%20harmful%20to%20their%20health%20or%20development;%20and%20(b)%20not%20such%20as%20to%20prejudice%20their%20attendance%20at%20school,%20their%20participation%20in%20vocational%20orientation%20or%20training%20programmes%20approved%20by%20the%20competent%20authority%20or%20their%20capacity%20to%20benefit%20from%20the%20instruction%20received&rsquo;.%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3EWhile%20child%20labor%20takes%20many%20different%20forms,%20a%20priority%20is%20to%20eliminate%20without%20delay%20the%20worst%20forms%20of%20child%20labor%20as%20defined%20by%20Article%203%20of%20ILO%20Convention%20This%20includes%20all%20forms%20of%20slavery%20or%20practices&nbsp;similar%20to%20slavery%20(such%20as%20sale,%20trafficking,%20forced%20or%20compulsory%20labor,%20serfdom,%20recruitment%20for%20armed%20conflict);%20the%20use,%20procuring%20or%20offering%20of%20a%20child%20for%20prostitution%20or%20illicit%20activities%20and%20any%20work%20that%20is%20likely%20to%20harm%20the%20health,%20safety%20or%20morals%20of%20children.%20ILO%20Convention%20182%20is%20intended%20to%20set%20priorities%20for%20states;%20however,%20organizations%20are%20expected%20not%20to%20use%20this%20convention%20to%20justify%20forms%20of%20child%20labor.%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3EChild%20labor%20results%20in%20under-skilled%20and%20unhealthy%20workers%20for%20tomorrow%20and%20perpetuates%20poverty%20across%20generations,%20thus%20impeding%20sustainable%20development.%20The%20abolition%20of%20child%20labor%20is%20therefore%20necessary%20for%20both%20economic%20and%20human%20development.%3C/div%3E",
